  "texts": [
    "Neural network architectures are fundamental to DL, consisting of interconnected layers and nodes that process and relay feature maps, enabling high-level abstraction in learning and prediction.",
    "To introduce the non-linearity to the network, activation functions, such as sigmoid, hyperbolic tangent (tanh), and Rectified Linear Unit (ReLU), are applied to the output of the network layers.",
    "For example, the ReLU function returns the input value unchanged if it is positive, and zero if it is negative.",
    "This non-linearity helps the network learn and model more complex patterns.",
    "Neural networks are updated through backpropagation, where errors (quantified as loss) are used to iteratively adjust connection weights, enhancing model precision."
  ],
